                \b The conflicts culminated in the Thirty Years' War, which devastated Germany and killed one third of its population, 
                \b a mortality rate twice that of World War I.
                \b The Peace of Westphalia broadly resolved the conflicts by recognising three separate Christian traditions in the Holy Roman Empire: 
                \b Roman Catholicism, Lutheranism and Calvinism.
                \b Although many European leaders were sickened by the bloodshed by 1648, 
                \b smaller religious wars continued to be waged until the 1710s, 
                \b including the Wars of the Three Kingdoms (1639-1651) on the British Isles, 
                \b the Savoyard-Waldensian wars (1655-1690), 
